<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Precedent1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Precedent</orth> <emph>(precédent),</emph> adj. former: <cit><quote>our own p. passions do instruct us what levity's in youth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.133" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 133</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>your p. lord,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 98</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy p. services,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 14, 83</bibl></cit>.
